This file gives an overview of how to setup NGRT4N.

First, note that NGRT4N Software is released under the terms the GPL License (version 3). 
Prior to the installation, you may need to read this license offer. See the COPYING file. 
 
INSTALL THE DAEMON MODULE
---------------
Dependencies
 - gcc-c++ >= 4.6.3
 - make
 - libzmq (librairies and development files)
 
Installation
  $ tar zxf ngrt4nX.Y.Y.tar.gz  # X.Y.Z refers to the version
  $ cd ngrt4nX.Y
  $ sudo ./install-sh -m daemon 

 
INSTALL THE UI MODULE
-------------
Dependencies
 - gcc-c++ >= 4.6.3
 - Qt >= 4.6.3 (required modules : QtCore, QtGui, QtSvg, QtWebKit, QtXml)
 - libzmq (librairies and development files)
 - graphviz
 
Installation
  $ tar zxf ngrt4nX.Y.Y.tar.gz  # X.Y.Z refers to the version
  $ cd ngrt4nX.Y 
  $ sudo ./install-sh -m ui
  
INSTALL ALL THE MODULES
  $ tar zxf ngrt4nX.Y.Y.tar.gz  # X.Y.Z refers to the version
  $ cd ngrt4nX.Y 
  $ sudo ./install-sh -m all
  
After the installation, check the online documentation for further processing (http://ngrt4n.com).
